      "content": "it doesn't feel like burnout though. it just feels... empty. like i'm just a series of notifications and emails. if i didn't log in tomorrow, or the day after, my boss would just hire someone else, my neighbors wouldn't even know i was gone, and my family would just see a ghost in a chat window. it's like i'm already not really there. it would be so quiet if i just... faded out. wouldn't it?",
